Postel's principle: "be conservative in what you do, be liberal<br>
in what you accept from others" was doctrine in early HTML<br>
specs, and led to disastrous disagreement among browsers'<br>
interpretation of web pages. Sadly, the "principle" lives on <br>
despite its having been expunged from the HTML spec.<br>
